Bit.Name: sdmmc1_not_default_af
Bit.Description: 0: SDMMC1 uses default hard coded AFMUX. 1: SDMMC1 uses AFMUX defined in OTP

Bit.Name: sdmmc2_not_default_af
Bit.Description: 0: SDMMC2 uses default hard coded AFMUX. 1: SDMMC2 uses AFMUX defined in OTP

Bit.Name: no_cpu_pll
Bit.Description: 0: PLLs for CPU/AXI are enable for cold boot. 1: PLLs for CPU/AXI are not enable for cold boot

Bit.Name: uart_instances_disabled
Bit.Description: Disable instance 0x1: USART2 0x2: USART5 0x4: USART6 0x8: USART8 0x10: USART9

Bit.Name: no_data_cache
Bit.Description: 0:Data cache is used by bootrom 1:Data cache is not used by bootrom

Bit.Name: boot_source_disable
Bit.Description: Disable boot source 0x1: FMC 0x2: QSPI NOR 0x4: eMMC 0x8: SD 0x10: UART

Bit.Name: fmc_force_sw_reset
Bit.Description: 0: Use RCC to reset FMC. 1: Use software procedure to reset FMC without impacting CM33.

Bit.Name: iomgr_port
Bit.Description: IOMGR port connected to OCTOSPI1, 0: Port 1, 1: Port 2

Bit.Name: iomgr_mux
Bit.Description: IOMGR mux is enabled: 0: no. 1: yes

Bit.Name: HSE value
Bit.Description: 0: HSE is autodetected 1: 24 MHz, 2: 25 MHz, 3: 26 MHz, 4: 19.2 MHz, 5: 40 MHz, 6: 48 MHz

Bit.Name: snand_need_plane_select_1
Bit.Description: 0:SPI NAND plane select not need, 1:SPI NAND plane select is needed

Bit.Name: pnand_number_of_ecc_bits_1
Bit.Description: 0 (unset): ECC unset - 1 (hamming): ECC 1bit (Hamming) - 2 (bch4): ECC 4bit (BCH4) - 3 (bch8): ECC 8bit (BCH8) - 4 (ondie): on-die ECC

Bit.Name: nand_nb_of_blocks_1
Bit.Description: Number of blocks in unit of 256 blocks

Bit.Name: nand_block_size
Bit.Description: 0:64 pages per block, 1:128 pages per block 2:256 pages per block

Bit.Name: pnand_param_stored_in_otp
Bit.Description: 0:No, 1:Nand parameters define in bank1 or bank2,

Bit.Name: secure_boot
Bit.Description: 0 (unlocked): device is in CLOSED_UNLOCKED state. Secure boot is not enforced (FSBL authentication is not mandatory). [1-15] (locked): device is in CLOSED_LOCKED state. Secure boot is enforced (FSBL authentication is mandatory).

Bit.Name: prov_done
Bit.Description: 0: RSSE provisioning is not done [1-15]: RSSE provisioning is done

Bit.Name: debug_lock
Bit.Description: 0: does not lock debug enabling [1-15]: locks debug enabling

Bit.Name: otp_prov_done
Bit.Description: 0: RSSe OTP provisioning is not done [1-15]: RSSe OTP provisioning part done, used to manage RSSe extension issue

Bit.Name: nb_added_stsecrets
Bit.Description: Nb of OTP words located in upper area [360-nb_added_stsecrets..359] that were provisioned (in encrypted mode) with ST secrets. Those will be decoded and used by RSSE firmware. Coding up to 64 ST secrets to provision in EWS (with DEV_BOOT).

Bit.Name: rsse_nb_attempts
Bit.Description: Monotonic counter to check the number of RSSe retry when an issue occurred during the provisioning process. The number is limited to 4 retries.

Bit.Name: snand_need_plane_select_2
Bit.Description: 0 (no): Serial NAND plane select is not needed 1 (yes): Serial NAND plane select is need

Bit.Name: pnand_number_of_ecc_bits_2
Bit.Description: 0 (unset): ECC unset 1 (hamming): ECC 1bit (Hamming) 2 (bch4): ECC 4bit (BCH4) 3 (bch8): ECC 8bit (BCH8) 4 (ondie): on-die ECC

Bit.Name: pnand_bus_width_2
Bit.Description: 0 (8-bits): data width is 8-bits 1 (16-bits): data width is 16-bits

Bit.Name: nand_block_size_2
Bit.Description: [1-4]: Block size in number of pages

Bit.Name: nand_page_size_2
Bit.Description: 0 (64): 64 pages per block 1 (128): 128 pages per block 2 (256): 256 pages per block

Bit.Name: rng_htcr_value
Bit.Description: 0: default value, RNG HTCR not modified 1: 0xA2B3 2: 0xAA74 3: 0xA6BA 4: 0x9AAE 5: 0x72AC 6: 0xAAC7 other: default value, RNG HTCR not modified

Bit.Name: ospi_io_speed_ovrw
Bit.Description: 0 (no): OSPI io speed is not overwritten by otp configuration 1 (yes): OSPI io speed is overwritten by otp configuration

Bit.Name: ospi_io_speed_clk_nclk
Bit.Description: 0b00 (low): low speed. 0b01 (medium): medium speed. 0b10 (high): high speed 0b11 (very_high): very high speed

Bit.Name: ospi_io_speed_data_cs
Bit.Description: 0b00 (low): low speed. 0b01 (medium): medium speed. 0b10 (high): high speed 0b11 (very_high): very high speed

Bit.Name: rssefw_version_monotonic_counter
Bit.Description: Monotonic version number of RSSe FW [1-0xFFFF] - [1-32]: Value of monotonic counter is X where X is position of the most significant bit at 1.

Bit.Name: oem_active_signing_key2
Bit.Description: monotonic key index of active signing key used for OEM-FSBLM authentication when second set of OEM keys is enabled.

Bit.Name: HSLV_VDDIO4
Bit.Description: VDDIO4 I/O segment below 2.5 V for I/O mode.

Bit.Name: HSLV_VDDIO3
Bit.Description: VDDIO3 I/O segment below 2.5 V for I/O mode.

Bit.Name: HSLV_VDDIO2
Bit.Description: VDDIO2 I/O segment below 2.5 V for I/O mode.

Bit.Name: HSLV_VDDIO1
Bit.Description: VDDIO1 I/O segment below 2.5 V for I/O mode.

Bit.Name: HSLV_VDD
Bit.Description: Main I/O segment below 2.5 V for I/O mode

Bit.Name: SYSRAM_ERASE
Bit.Description: 0: SYSRAM upper half not erased on reset 1: SYSRAM upper half erased on reset

Bit.Name: DISABLE_SCAN
Bit.Description: Scan chains are disabled on CLOSED_UNLOCKED device when this bit is 1
